request.description:
POST /api/Categories

DTO: CreateCategoryRequestDto { Name, UrlHandle }
Returns: CategoryDto { Id, Name, UrlHandle }

PUT /api/Categories/{id:guid}

DTO: UpdateCategoryRequestDto { Name, UrlHandle }
Returns: 204 NoContent on success, 404 NotFound if not found

GET /api/BlogPosts/{id}

No auth required. Increments ViewCount. Calculates ReadingTimeMinutes dynamically (200 wpm, min 1).
Returns: BlogPostDto with categories, readingTimeMinutes, viewCount.

GET /api/BlogPosts/urlHandle/{urlHandle}
[AllowAnonymous]

Lookup by URL-friendly slug. Increments ViewCount.

GET /api/BlogPosts/stats
[Authorize(Roles = "Admin")]

Returns: DashboardStatsDto { TotalPosts, PublishedPosts, DraftPosts, DeletedPosts }

DELETE /api/BlogPosts/{id}
[Authorize(Roles = "Admin")]

Sets IsDeleted=true (soft delete). Returns 204 NoContent or 404.

PUT /api/BlogPosts/restore/{id:Guid}
[Authorize(Roles = "Admin")]

Sets IsDeleted=false. Returns 200 OK or 404.

DELETE /api/BlogPosts/hard-delete/{id:Guid}
[Authorize(Roles = "Admin")]

Permanently removes the post from the database. Returns 200 OK or 404.

item.description:
Comment creation (requires any auth), listing by post, and deletion (owner or Admin).

DTO: CreateCommentRequestDto { Content [Required], BlogPostId [Required] }
Response: CommentDto { Id, Content, BlogPostId, UserId, UserEmail, DateAdded }

request.description:
BlogPostRepository throws generic Exception('Blog post not found.') when ID doesn't exist.
GlobalExceptionHandler catches this → maps unhandled Exception to 500.
Response: { message: 'Blog post not found.', statusCode: 500 }
